The Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE) has listed additional 31.515 million ordinary shares of 50 kobo each of Stanbic IBTC Holdings Plc on its Daily Official List. The NSE said the additional shares were admitted on the NSE on December 19, 2019, saying that he additional shares of 31.515 million ordinary shares of 50 Kobo each arose as a result of the Scrip Dividend offered to eligible shareholders of Stanbic IBTC who elected to receive ordinary shares in lieu of cash dividends with respect to the N1.00 final dividend declared for the half year ended 30 June 2019. According to NSE, with this listing of 31.515 million ordinary shares, the total issued and fully paid up shares of the Company has now increased from 10.473 billion to 10.505 billion ordinary shares. It will be recalled that the Holdings company in its third quarter results ended September 30, 2019 reported gross earnings of N176.1 billion, an increase of 4.3 per cent when compared to N168.8 billion as at September last year. Interest income also increased by 3.5 per cent to N91 billion during the nine months period, up from N87.9 billion last year.